<p>The diagram displays:</p>

<p><strong>Entities:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Locations:</strong> Stores location information.</li>
  <li><strong>Characters:</strong> Stores character details with a foreign key to Locations.</li>
  <li><strong>Episodes:</strong> Stores episodes information.</li>
  <li><strong>Quotes:</strong> Join table connecting Characters and Episodes with quote text.</li>
  <li><strong>Appearance:</strong> Pure join table for the many-to-many relationship between Characters and Episodes.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Relationships:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>Locations → Characters (1:many)</li>
  <li>Characters → Quotes (1:many)</li>
  <li>Episodes → Quotes (1:many)</li>
  <li>Characters → Appearances (1:many)</li>
  <li>Episodes → Appearances (1:many)</li>
</ul>